external_knowledge:
- Blossoms refer to the tests;
- Blooming successfully means the tests were successful;
- Flourished refers to the completion of the test within a response time;
- Gardens symbolize the environments where the tests took place;
- Moments of blooming denote the execution times of the tests;
- Time to fully blossom refers to the response time of the tests.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(log_id) AS info_logs_count
FROM test_logs
WHERE log_level = 'INFO';

SELECT t.test_name, r.response_code
FROM tests t
INNER JOIN test_results r ON t.test_id = r.test_id;

external_knowledge:
- Test type can be considered as different categories of tests, analogous to different waves in an ocean;
- Average duration for each test type represents the height of each wave;
- A running average can be visualized as a growing wave that incorporates the height of each wave as it passes, providing a cumulative height.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS successful_test_count
FROM test_results
WHERE success = 1;
